  <description type="morphology">Plants 0.1–1.2 cm. Stem leaves contorted when dry, wide-spreading and distinctly 3-ranked when moist, ovate-lanceolate, 1.5–4 mm; base decurrent; margins plane to weakly reflexed proximally, serrulate distally; apex acute; costa narrow, ending in or just before apex; inner laminal cells smaller, walls thicker than marginal cells. Sexual condition dioicous. Seta 3–10 cm. Capsule 3–4.5 mm. Spores 33–38 µm.</description>
